@WenbinZhu  I understand that this check is trying to fast fail to avoid more task being spawned. For those not completed in allFutures , it seems like calling completeExceptionally does not  cancel tasks behind CF, which means those tasks still consuming resources silently for a while.
According to official doc:

If not already completed, causes invocations of {@link #get()}
* and related methods to throw the given exception.

Is it possible to assign an executor when creating tasks by cf? And once we got an exception, we can shutdownNow that executor.

